crane shot, wide shot, push-in / dolly in, wide-angle lens, high contrast lighting, backlighting, dawn time / sunrise time, mixed colors, cinematic, photorealistic, highly detailed, 8k, smoke, surreal

A grand and smooth crane shot sweeps over a vast range of snow-covered mountains. It is dawn, and the rising sun kisses the distant peaks with golden light while casting long, cold-blue shadows in the valleys. As the camera slowly pushes in, cresting a final, sharp ridge, an impossible sight is revealed: a vibrant, circular oasis thriving miraculously on the summit of the mountain. At the center of the oasis is a geothermal hot spring, emitting wisps of steam that create a stark, high-contrast visual against the surrounding snow. The turquoise water of the spring provides a warm focal point in the cool-toned landscape. Around the spring, on warm, moss-covered rocks, grow exotic, bioluminescent plants and a few resilient, ancient pine trees. The strong backlighting from the low sun makes the steam and the sparkling ice crystals at the edge of the snow brilliantly luminous. This warm-toned pocket of life creates an extreme and surreal contrast with the sharp, cold, and desolate world of ice and rock around it, evoking a sacred, tranquil, and wondrously otherworldly feeling.
